LICENSE NOTICE — learn-a-hanzi
================================

This file records the licensing *intent* for the project. Final license terms for any
distributed data are to be confirmed against upstream sources before public release —
see docs/specs/02-data-sources.md (sections "License obligations summary" and the ⚠ flags).

1. APPLICATION SOURCE CODE
   -------------------------
   Intended license: MIT OR Apache-2.0 (to be chosen before first release).
   Until chosen, this source code is © its authors; all rights reserved for the code,
   except as required to honor the upstream data licenses below.

2. DERIVED LEARNING DATA (the bundled SQLite dataset)
   ---------------------------------------------------
   Built from open datasets, each under its own license. The combined dataset inherits the
   most restrictive applicable terms (likely CC-BY-SA 3.0 share-alike from CC-CEDICT, plus
   the Arphic Public License conditions from make-me-a-hanzi graphics). Confirm before
   redistribution.

   Upstream sources and their licenses (⚠ verify current text before release):

   - make-me-a-hanzi (chanind/make-me-a-hanzi)
       graphics.txt, dictionary.txt → stroke paths, medians, definitions
       License: Arphic Public License

   - CC-CEDICT (https://www.mdbg.net/chinese/dictionary?page=cedict)
       multi-char words, definitions cross-check
       License: CC-BY-SA 3.0

   - Unihan database (unicode.org)
       frequency ranks, radical/stroke metadata
       License: Unicode Data Files agreement

   - Tatoeba (tatoeba.org)
       example sentences + translation links
       License: CC-BY 2.0 FR (per-sentence attribution recorded)

3. ATTRIBUTION
   -------------
   A Credits screen in the app lists these sources and (where the license requires) the
   individual contributors whose data is bundled.
